The data are aggregated into 5-year intervals. The data are stratified by county of residence, maternal age , maternal race/ethnicity and infant gender. The data are from an active surveillance system that ascertains birth defects among live births, fetal deaths, and terminations, using ICD-9 codes.</dct:description>
